============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is quantum mechanics?
A1: Quantum mechanics describes physics at atomic and
     subatomic scales. Key principles: wave-particle
     duality, uncertainty principle, superposition, and
     quantum entanglement.

Q2: What is the Renaissance?
A2: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q3: What is osmosis?
A3: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q4: What is inflation?
A4: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

Q5: What is natural selection?
A5: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

